div.div:
Three years into her life as a shut-in, vampire Terakomari Gandesblood (Komari for short), awakens to find she’s been appointed as a Commander in the Mulnite Imperial Army! The thing is, her new unit consists solely of belligerent ruffians who revolt against their superiors at the slightest hint of weakness. Although Komari hails from a line of vampires as powerful as they are prestigious, her refusal to drink blood has made her the picture of mediocrity—scrawny, un-coordinated, and inept at magic. With the odds stacked against her, will the help of her trusty (and slightly infatuated) maid Vill be enough for this recluse to blunder her way to success? Or will Komari rue the day she ever left the safety of her room?
(Source: Yen Press)
Shingeki no Kyojin: The Final Season

It’s been four years since the Scout Regiment reached the shoreline, and the world looks different now. Things are heating up as the fate of the Scout Regiment—and the people of Paradis—are determined at last. However, Eren is missing. Will he reappear before age-old tensions between Marleyans and Eldians result in the war of all wars?
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Fukushuu Kansuisha no Jinsei Nishuume Isekaitan THE COMIC

Five years ago, in the middle of winter, Kosuke Kurono's beloved sister was raped and murdered. Ever since then, he has devoted his life to revenge. When he finally avenged his sister's death, Kurono had nothing left to live for, and he decided to end his own life, too. But instead, he was reincarnated into another world, and given the Black Magic wielded by the great heroes of the past. Being told that his sister might have reincarnated into this world, too, he set out to look for her!

(Source: Comic Ride, translated)
Otome Game no Mob desura naindaga
Comedy, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

Taichi was reincarnated as Isaac, an apprentice gardener in the world of an otome game. But, looking back, Isaac wasn't even part of the game... This is the story of the interweaving lives of the Duke's daughter, Lydia, and a boy who isn't even an NPC.
(Source: MANGA UP!)
